bib.title: Experimental study of the spectroscopic factors of90-97Zr

free_txt: The Q3D magnetic spectrograph has a
high-energy resolution of about 0.02%. The reaction
products were separated by Q3D and then measured by a
silicon detector (PSSD) at the focal plane.
The diameter of the target chamber was 479 mm,
and the accepted solid angle of Q3D magnetic
spectrometer was set to be 0.34 +- 0.01 msr for
excellent angular resolution. A movable Faraday cup
was placed behind the target to monitor the beam
intensity. A dE-E detector telescopic system was set
at about 23 deg downstream of the reaction target for
the cross check of the beam intensity.
